<title>UK: Ex-dividends to take 2.925 points off FTSE-100.</title>
<headline>Ex-dividends to take 2.925 points off FTSE-100.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following FTSE-100 stocks will trade ex-dividend on January 6. Analysts estimate this will take 2.925 points off the FTSE 100.</p>
<p>							 DIVIDEND	INDEX</p>
<p>							 (PENCE)	 EFFECT</p>
<p>		  COMPANY			   Net    Gross    Gross</p>
<p>    * EMI Group Plc			     8.00   10.00    0.253</p>
<p>    * Granada Group Plc			 8.77   10.96    0.545</p>
<p>    * Grand Metropolitan Plc		 10.05   12.56    1.538</p>
<p>    * Railtrack Group Plc		     7.30    9.13    0.266</p>
<p>    * Scottish &amp; Newcastle Plc		7.21    9.01    0.323</p>
